HEADWORD: Pentachord
<hw>Pen"ta*chord</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pentachordus</ets> five-stringed, Gr. <grk>penta`chordos</grk>;
<grk>penta-</grk> five + <grk>chordh`</grk> string.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An ancient instrument of music with five strings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An order or system of five sounds.</def>
